views.text: At Wise Psychology, we are dedicated to providing our clients with the support and guidance they need to achieve their goals and improve their mental health. We offer various services, including individual therapy and couples therapy, to help our clients address various concerns and challenges.
views.desc: <button bound_box=60,72,1020,75>At Wise Psychology, we are dedicated to providing </button>

views.text: Our team of highly trained and experienced psychologists is committed to providing evidence-based care tailored to each individual's unique needs. We take the time to get to know our clients and understand their concerns in order to develop a personalised treatment plan that is effective and sustainable.
views.desc: <button bound_box=60,72,1020,75>Our team of highly trained and experienced psychol</button>

views.text: We also understand that life can be busy, and difficult to find time for therapy. That's why we offer convenient and flexible appointments, including evening options. We provide both video and phone services, so you can access the support you need from your home or workplace without having to travel.
views.desc: <button bound_box=60,72,1020,75>We also understand that life can be busy, and diff</button>

views.text: At Wise Psychology, we believe that everyone deserves access to high-quality mental health care. That's why we accept a wide range of third-party funding plans such as Medicare, TAC, WorkCover, and Private Health Insurance and offer sliding scale fees for students and self-funded clients.

views.text: If you're ready to take the next step in your journey to better mental health, we encourage you to visit our website at www.wise-psychology.com to learn more about our services or schedule an appointment now in HotDoc. We look forward to working with you!

views.text: When you make an appointment, you reserve that time exclusively for you. When appointments are cancelled at late notice, it is not usually practicable to fill that time slot. If you cancel or reschedule fewer than 48 hours before the appointment, a cancellation fee of 50% of the total appointment cost will apply. If you cancel or reschedule fewer than 24 hours before the appointment or do not attend the session, you must pay the total appointment cost. Medicare reimbursement can not be claimed for cancelled, rescheduled or missed appointments. For further information, please refer to the service Terms of Use. Sessions will be considered ‘not attended’ 20 minutes after the scheduled start time. If you arrive 20 minutes or more after the scheduled start time, the session will be considered cancelled, and relevant fees will apply.
